    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil Pump - Installation - High-pressure Oil Pump</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26511.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump</title>
        <figure id="e3001218" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil pump assembly inlet and branch tube adapter O-rings</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter O-ring seal recess</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter O-ring seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure pump inlet O-ring seal, #207</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate and place a new O-ring onto the high-pressure oil pump inlet recess, and one onto
                the branch tube assembly (O-ring recess) for the branch tube adapter.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use only approved pump to cover seal. Substitution could cause damage to
                    the pump cover.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001219" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1397.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the high-pressure oil pump cover O-ring (shown with the branch tube adapter removed)
            </caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring onto the high-pressure oil pump to cover recess.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, connect the branch tube adapter to the high-pressure oil pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001220" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the high-pressure oil pump</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the high-pressure oil pump with attached branch tube adapter.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001221" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque the high-pressure oil pump bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, take extra care to not drop these bolts. These bolts are not captured
                    within the high-pressure oil pump.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three Torx&#174; socket bolts (M8 x 45) to secure the high-pressure pump to the
                crankcase. Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two branch tube adapter bolts (M6 x 30) to the branch tube assembly to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
